article.headline: Buffalo 64, Kent St. 53
article.story: AMHERST, N.Y. -- Rodney Pierce scored 18 points to help Buffalo beat Kent State 64-53 on Wednesday night. Pierce went 4-for-5 from 3-point range for the Bulls (11-5, 3-1 Mid-American Conference), who snapped a seven-game losing streak against the Golden Flashes. Al Fisher had 26 points for Kent State (8-10, 1-3). Julian Sullinger had 11 points and six rebounds. Buffalo led 28-23 at halftime despite shooting just 37.9 percent. The Bulls made just 10 of 17 foul shots but shot 43 percent for the game and outrebounded Kent State 39-29. The Golden Flashes shot 41 percent from the field and 7-for-12 from the line.
